.TH TAGRD 1
.SH NAME
tagrd \- plumb a Mifare Ultralight tag
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tagrd
[
.B -D
]
.B /dev/cci*/rpc
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Tagrd
runs continuously, polling a
.IR usb (4)
ccid-based
Touchatag
reader and plumbs
a message for any tag with its content and its UID.
It plumbs another message when the
tag disappears.
For an example of how to use this, see
.BR /sys/src/cmd/scard/plumbing .
.PP
When the program successfully communicates with the reader,
its led should turn orange.
.PP
This program is part of an ongoing programming of the ISO smartcard
standards, part of the library can be seen at
.BR /sys/src/cmd/scard .
.PD
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/scard/tagrd.c
.br
.B /sys/src/cmd/scard/plumbing
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR usb (4)
